title: 10 Min All-Out Elliptical HIIT Workout
description:
Pressed for time, but still want to achieve an effective cardiovascular workout on your elliptical? Follow along with Sunny Trainer Sydney for 10 minutes of all-out interval work on your elliptical at home. If you have time, repeat it twice for an even bigger calorie burn! 

10 Min All-Out Elliptical HIIT Workout
Workout Length: 10-Minute
Workout Level: Beginner/Intermediate
Sunny Trainer: Sydney Eaton 

WORKOUT DETAILS
0:00 | Intro

WARMUP 
0:24 | Warmup – 60 sec
 
EASY PACE, PROGRESSIVE – 60 SEC
INTERVALS – RESISTANCE OF CHOICE (REPEAT 8 TIMES!)
1:28 | All-Out Pace: Set 1 – 30 sec
1:57 | Rest: Set 1 – 30 sec
2:27 | All-Out Pace: Set 2 – 30 sec
2:58 | Rest: Set 2 – 30 sec
3:28 | All-Out Pace: Set 3 – 30 sec
3:58 | Rest: Set 3 – 30 sec
4:28 | All-Out Pace: Set 4 – 30 sec
4:58 | Rest: Set 4 – 30 sec
5:30 | All-Out Pace: Set 5 – 30 sec
5:59 | Rest: Set 5 – 30 sec
6:27 | All-Out Pace: Set 6 – 30 sec
7:00 | Rest: Set 6 – 30 sec
7:29 | All-Out Pace: Set 7 – 30 sec
7:57 | Rest: Set 7 – 30 sec
8:29 | All-Out Pace: Set 8 – 30 sec

COOLDOWN
8:59 | Cooldown – 60 sec

END WORKOUT

comments:
I found this workout last week.
I bought the machine 5 months ago.
I had neck surgery and an ablation done, and I gained weight horribly.
I was doing it slow till I got to walk it to 2 miles.
Since I started thus workout been going slow, today I completed the workout in full.
My husband looks at me and says he is very proud for sticking with it.

I love all the sunny health elliptical workouts, they are so motivational. Without them, I would just do 20 min flat and maybe push myself once or twice and get fed up. I've saved your elliptical playlist to have fast access to them all to choose from. An immense thanks for putting the workouts out there for free.

I’m 55 and I work a 50 + hour week.  And this workout is perfect. Only 10 minutes. Just awesome.  I’ve dusted my machine off and I’m doing this work out .  So glad I came across your video. Thank you!  💕

This is so good!! I am overweight  and have asthma, so exercising is challenging... anyway I work out to this video three times a week for 20 min now (I do the video twice). I started doing this and the goal was to be out of breath everyday for 10 min.... I had to pause because I couldn't keep up... within a month I do this 3 times a week for 20 min! Next goal is 30min! I started changing my lifestyle before is started to exercise and I lost a total of 12kg! Let's go!!! 20 more!!! Thank you Sydney!!

After a stroke 3 years ago when 68 I changed earring habits and now do cardio & light weights. I gone from 14.5stone to 10 st 10 lbs. The elliptical workouts like this one have been the backbone of my cardio as I have rheumatoid arthritis and 5 dropped bones in my feet so running hurts big time. Glad to report that I have recorded 3 mins 38 secs for 1 mile and 8 mins 20 for 2 mile sprints but mostly do 10 min & 30 min HIIT on elliptical Nordic track 9.5 machine. Helps me relax, sleep better and feel pretty good for 71 today.
